X = df.iloc[:, :-1].to_numpy()
y = df['age'].to_numpy()


X_train, X_hold, y_train, y_hold = train_test_split(X, y, train_size=0.6, random_state=11)


X_valid, X_test, y_valid, y_test = train_test_split(X_hold, y_hold, test_size=0.5, random_state=11)
In [ ]:
reg = MLPRegressor(hidden_layer_sizes=(100, 100, 100, 100, 100),
                   max_iter=10, activation='relu', batch_size=100, random_state=22,
                   solver="adam", verbose=False,
                   learning_rate_init=.001, warm_start=True, early_stopping=False)

# This model optimizes the squared error.

training_mse = []
validation_mse = []
test_mse = []

However, Adam applies extra scaling to the gradient, so the learning rate is applied to this transformation of the gradient, not the gradient itself. This can't be turned off because this is the essence of the algorithm

In [ ]:
for epoch in range(26):
    reg.fit(X_train, y_train)
    Y_pred1 = reg.predict(X_train)
    curr_train_score = mean_squared_error(y_train, Y_pred1) 

    Y_pred2 = reg.predict(X_valid)
    curr_valid_score = mean_squared_error(y_valid, Y_pred2) 

    training_mse.append(curr_train_score)                  
    validation_mse.append(curr_valid_score)

    Test_for_the_sake_of_it = reg.predict(X_test)
    curr_test_score = mean_squared_error(y_test, Test_for_the_sake_of_it) 

    test_mse.append(curr_test_score)             
    if epoch == 10:
        Y_pred3 = reg.predict(X_test)
        df_temp = pd.DataFrame({'Actual': Y_pred3, 'Predicted': y_test})
        display(df_temp)
        MSE_on_test = mean_squared_error(Y_pred3, y_test)
        print(MSE_on_test)
        MAE_on_test = mean_absolute_error(Y_pred3, y_test)
        print(MAE_on_test)

grid_func = MLPRegressor(hidden_layer_sizes=(100, ),
                   max_iter=50, activation='relu', batch_size=100, random_state=22,
                   solver="adam", learning_rate="constant", verbose=False,
                   learning_rate_init=.001, warm_start=True, early_stopping=False)


param_grid = {
    'hidden_layer_sizes': [(100, 100, 50), (100, ), (100, 100), (50, 50, 50, 50, 50, 50)],
    'max_iter': [120, 250],
    'activation': ['relu', 'tanh'],
    'learning_rate_init': [0.01, 0.001],
    'solver': ['adam'],
}

grid = GridSearchCV(grid_func, param_grid=param_grid, n_jobs= -1, cv=5, refit=True, verbose=1, return_train_score=True)


grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
test_result = grid.predict(X_test)
df_temp = pd.DataFrame({'Actual': test_result, 'Predicted': y_test})
display(df_temp)
MSE_on_test = mean_squared_error(test_result, y_test)
print(MSE_on_test) 

print(grid.score(X_train, y_train)) #
print(grid.best_params_)
